  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "One might expect that such manipulations strongly modulate the effects of saliency maps.",
    "Surprisingly, this is not supported by the available evidence.",
    "In fact, the quality of saliency maps had little impact on performance (Chu et al., 2020; Leemann et al., 2023; Maehigashi et al., 2023a).",
    "For instance, participants' accuracy in classifying the age of faces did not differ between normal and distorted saliency maps (Chu et al., 2020).",
    "Presumably, the impacts of saliency map quality are weak and thus drown in the high variance caused by other factors such as the ambiguity of images (Leemann et al., 2023) or the type of dataset (Maehigashi et al., 2023b)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
